                  <div id="versionCompareContent" class="WPC-editableContent">
                    Baron Mode is also known as &quot;Forced Attack&quot; or Player Killing (PKing). This mode of PvP does not have to be accepted by a target family. Baron mode is available for families on PK servers (currently Bristia and Illier in SotNW) after they reach <a href="/page/Family+Level+-+Barracks" target="_self">Family Level</a> 5. To Enter Baron Mode, right-click on another family over fam lvl 5 and select &quot;Enter Baron Mode&quot;. Both you and your target family are removed from your squads, and now EVERYONE can attack you, even your clanmates. Baron PKing causes Exp loss to characters that are killed, however, Baron families lose more exp upon death than their targets. Barons also drop items upon death.<br>
                    <br>
                    Baron mode has different Levels depending on how many characters the family kills. Each kill gives Baron Value which is like points (you can see them on Alt+R). Your <i>first kill</i> after Entering Baron Mode gives you 2000 Baron Value automatically. Each subsequent kill gives you additional points equal to the level of the person you killed (If you kill a level 50 character, you get 50 Baron Value, if you kill an Expert level 3 character you get 112 Baron Value). Baron Level is assigned based on Baron points and gives you buffs like so:<br>
                    <ul>
                      <li><font size="2"><b>Baron level 1</b> - 1 baron points. Buff: ATK +5%, DEF -5. Red skull appears overhead.<br></font></li>
                      <li><b><font size="2">Baron level</font></b> <font size="2"><b>2</b> - 2500 baron point</font><font size="2">s. Buff: ATK +10%, DEF -10. Red skull with ring appears overhead.<br></font></li>
                      <li><b><font size="2">Baron level</font></b> <font size="2"><b>3</b> - 5000 baron points</font><font size="2">. Buff: ATK +15%, DEF -15.</font></li>
                      <li><b><font size="2">Baron level</font></b> <font size="2"><b>4</b> - 10000 baron points</font><font size="2">. Buff: ATK +20%, DEF -20.</font></li>
                      <li><b><font size="2">Baron level</font></b> <font size="2"><b>5</b> - 20000 baron points</font><font size="2">. Buff: ATK +25%, DEF -25. Pulsing, glowing red skull with ring appears overhead.</font></li>
                    </ul>When a character of a Baron family is killed, it loses Exp and the family drops an item from its inventory to the ground; at higher baron levels the likelihood of a valuable item drop increases. Above Baron Level 2, <i>the item dropped may be an equipped item</i>. (You never drop any item that is described as &quot;cannot be dropped, traded or sold&quot;, like Ancestral gear.) This way you could lose your most valuable gear, so watch your Baron Value and be careful!<br>
                    <br>
                    As long as you have Baron Value, you remain hostile to all players. You can reduce your Baron Value by killing monsters. At 0 Baron Value you lose your baron mode (or if you enter baron mode but don&#39;t kill anyone, the mode automatically cancels after a few minutes or when you wipe or change zone).<br>
                    <br>
                    <h3>Baron City - Los Toldos</h3><font size="2">Los Toldos is the home city of the player killers. Once you enter baron mode, if you go to the quarters or get killed, you will be sent to Los Toldos instead of your home city. Here you can get unique items, and some quests.<br>
                    <br>
                    Talk to Johnny the Blacksmith while Baron to get the following <a href="/page/Back" target="_self">Back Costumes</a>, if you have the necessary Baron Value points and items to craft them.<br>
